name: isInverseOf
label: inverseOf
comment: The property that determines that two given properties are inverse.

name: isSameAs
label: sameAs
comment: The property that determines that two given individuals are equal.

name: propertyIsDisjointWith
label: propertyDisjointWith
comment: Used to specify that two properties are mutually disjoint, and it is defined as a property itself.

name: isEquivalentClass
label: equivalentClass
comment: The property that determines that two given classes are equivalent, and that is used to specify datatype definitions.

name: isDisjointWith
label: disjointWith
comment: The property that determines that two given properties are disjoint.

name: ToolkitLabel
label: ToolkitLabel
definition: Label for use in RDA Toolkit

name: ToolkitDefinition
label: ToolkitDefinition
definition: Definition for use in RDA Toolkit

name: SeeAlso
label: See Also
definition: 'See Also' for use in RDA Toolkit

name: ToolkitElementType
label: has element type
definition: This relates an element to a code (literal) that indicates how the element should be processed for use in the Toolkit CMS.

name: ToolkitTask
label: has task
definition: This relates an RDA element to a value taken from the new RDA value vocabulary "RDA User Tasks"

name: ToolkitPath
label: has path
definition: This relates an RDA element to a value taken from the new RDA value vocabulary "RDA Recording Methods"
